I'll give feedback a shot. Thoughts sort of in order. I like the explanation of this world. Perhaps too /adhg/ for me, but it seemed like you enjoyed noting details in it. I certainly liked some of the details noted in their character such as
>Alexandra stormed into the breakfast hall and scowled at her mother while bowing, more on reflex than any real show of respect for her mother.

Paragraphs should be spaced by the enter key. A few of them seem bunched together for no real reason. So press that enter key to keep things nice and clean when you want to start a new paragraph.

The dialogue is where my main gripes come in. If you don't take anything else from this post, please, for the sake of waifurs, always press the enter key when someone else starts talking, then orient the reader with a 'she/he/they/it/the woman/the man/the anything at all'.
Similarly, make sure to use commas or periods in dialogue when they come to an end. Commas for speech tags (said/replied etc. NOT asked, that always gets a question mark) or periods if you do not use one.
Let me do a quick alteration.
>"Where's Dalton?" Lady Alexandra asked.
>The maid nodded. "Let me call one in," she replied.
>"No, no, I meant MY Dalton. Mine," Alexandra corrected.
Keep these in mind, just for the sake of smooth reading.
